<h2>More Excellent Options</h2>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Louis Jadot Pouilly-Fuissé</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Burgundy, France | ~$28</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">This exceptional value Burgundian Chardonnay showcases the minerality and elegance of Mâconnais limestone soils. Crisp citrus and white flowers complement subtle oak integration, delivering authentic Burgundy character without the premium price tag.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Wine enthusiasts seeking authentic Burgundy on a budget</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Chateau Ste. Michelle Cold Creek Vineyard Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Columbia Valley, Washington | ~$25</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Washington's volcanic soils and cool climate create remarkable tension in this Chardonnay, balancing ripe stone fruit with vibrant acidity. The judicious use of French oak adds complexity without overwhelming the pure varietal character that defines Pacific Northwest winemaking.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Everyday drinking and pairing with Pacific Northwest cuisine</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Ramey Russian River Valley Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Russian River Valley, California | ~$45</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">David Ramey's masterful approach combines Burgundian techniques with California fruit intensity, creating wines with remarkable depth and precision. Cool-climate Russian River fog preserves natural acidity while allowing for full phenolic ripeness, resulting in a wine that's both powerful and elegant.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Special dinners and collectors appreciating California terroir</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Peter Michael La Carrière Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Knights Valley, California | ~$55</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-small">From volcanic Knights Valley soils, this Chardonnay exhibits extraordinary mineral complexity alongside rich tropical fruit flavors. Sir Peter Michael's commitment to Burgundian winemaking philosophy, including indigenous yeast fermentation and extended lees aging, produces a wine of remarkable sophistication and aging potential.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Wine collectors and special occasions requiring cellar-worthy elegance</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Domaine William Fèvre Chablis Premier Cru Montmains</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Chablis, France | ~$40</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Pure Kimmeridgian limestone terroir creates this wine's signature oyster shell minerality and razor-sharp precision. Fermented in stainless steel to preserve Chablis' distinctive character, this Premier Cru offers concentrated citrus fruit wrapped in an almost electric mineral framework that defines great Chablis.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Seafood pairings and Burgundy purists seeking mineral-driven wines</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Kosta Browne Kanzler Vineyard Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Russian River Valley, California | ~$75</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">This single-vineyard expression from Sebastopol Hills demonstrates how cool-climate Chardonnay can achieve both richness and finesse. Ancient Goldridge soils contribute to complex mineral layers beneath pristine Fuji apple and citrus blossom notes, while expertly managed French oak provides structure without masking terroir expression.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Wine enthusiasts seeking pinnacle California Chardonnay craftsmanship</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Domaine Henri Boillot Puligny-Montrachet</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Burgundy, France | ~$85</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">From the heart of Burgundy's white wine capital, this village-level Puligny showcases why this appellation commands global respect. Henri Boillot's traditional approach emphasizes terroir expression through minimal intervention, creating wines with haunting mineral precision and decades-long aging potential that justify their cult status.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Milestone celebrations and serious Burgundy collectors</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Evening Land Seven Springs Vineyard Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Eola-Amity Hills, Oregon | ~$38</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">This hidden gem showcases Oregon's emerging Chardonnay excellence through Burgundian clones planted in volcanic Jory soils. The cool Willamette Valley climate preserves natural acidity while allowing for complex flavor development, creating a wine that bridges Old World minerality with New World fruit expression in unexpected and delightful ways.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Adventurous wine lovers exploring Oregon's potential beyond Pinot Noir</p>
  </div>
</div>


<h2>More Excellent Options</h2>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Domaine William Fèvre Chablis</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Chablis, Burgundy | ~$25</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">A textbook example of mineral-driven Chardonnay from Kimmeridgian soils, offering pristine citrus and green apple flavors with that signature chalky backbone. This consistently excellent producer delivers authentic Chablis character without oak interference, showcasing pure terroir expression.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Oysters and shellfish, everyday luxury drinking</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Chateau Ste. Michelle Columbia Valley Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Columbia Valley, Washington | ~$12</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Washington's flagship winery produces this remarkable value that punches well above its price point. Balanced oak integration complements bright apple and pear fruit, while the cool climate preserves natural acidity that keeps the wine fresh and food-friendly.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Budget-conscious wine lovers, weeknight dinners</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Ramey Russian River Valley Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Russian River Valley, Sonoma | ~$45</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">David Ramey's masterful winemaking shines in this elegant expression that balances richness with restraint. Wild fermentation and subtle lees stirring create complex layers of stone fruit, hazelnut, and spice, while maintaining the cool-climate freshness that defines great Russian River Chardonnay.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Special dinners, collectors seeking refined California style</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Domaine Leflaive Puligny-Montrachet</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Puligny-Montrachet, Burgundy | ~$85</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">From biodynamic vineyards in Burgundy's white wine capital, this village-level bottling represents exceptional value from one of the region's most revered producers. Intense minerality meets elegant fruit concentration, with layers that unfold beautifully over years of cellaring.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Serious wine enthusiasts, milestone celebrations</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Kosta Browne Russian River Valley Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Russian River Valley, Sonoma | ~$55</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">This cult winery applies their precision-focused approach to Chardonnay with stunning results. Native yeast fermentation and French oak aging create a wine of remarkable complexity, featuring ripe tropical fruit balanced by bright acidity and mineral undertones from select vineyard sites.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Wine collectors, sophisticated entertaining</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Littorai Charles Heintz Vineyard Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Sonoma Coast | ~$65</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Ted Lemon's biodynamic approach and extreme coastal location create one of California's most Burgundian expressions. The combination of Dijon clones, indigenous fermentation, and minimal intervention winemaking produces a wine of extraordinary finesse and longevity that rivals the best of Chablis.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Burgundy lovers, cellaring enthusiasts</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Domaine de la Côte Bloom's Field Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Sta. Rita Hills, California | ~$42</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Rajat Parr's hidden gem showcases the untapped potential of this cool climate appellation. Planted to Burgundian selections in sandy soils just miles from the Pacific, this wine offers remarkable purity and tension, with saline minerality that speaks to its maritime proximity.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Adventurous wine lovers, discovering emerging regions</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Château des Tours Saumur Blanc</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Loire Valley, France | ~$18</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">This Loire Valley sleeper proves exceptional Chardonnay doesn't require California prices or Burgundy prestige. Grown on tuffeau limestone soils and fermented in old oak, it delivers crystalline purity with subtle complexity that pairs beautifully with goat cheese and fresh herbs.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Value hunters, French bistro-style dining</p>
  </div>
</div>


<h2>More Excellent Options</h2>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Domaine William Fèvre Chablis</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Chablis, Burgundy | ~$28</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">This quintessential Chablis showcases pure Kimmeridgian minerality with pristine citrus notes and subtle salinity. Fèvre's meticulous viticulture produces a wine that perfectly expresses terroir without oak interference, offering remarkable complexity for the price point.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Seafood dinners and those discovering authentic Burgundian Chardonnay</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Chateau Ste. Michelle Canoe Ridge Vineyard Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Columbia Valley, Washington | ~$25</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Crafted from Horse Heaven Hills fruit, this Chardonnay delivers exceptional value with its balanced approach to oak aging and bright acidity. The wine displays ripe stone fruit flavors complemented by vanilla and spice, showcasing Washington's ability to produce world-class Chardonnay.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Everyday drinking and introducing friends to quality American Chardonnay</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Rombauer Carneros Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Carneros, California | ~$42</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">This crowd-pleasing Chardonnay undergoes full malolactic fermentation and French oak aging, creating a rich, buttery texture with tropical fruit flavors. While unapologetically opulent, it maintains enough acidity to pair beautifully with cream-based dishes and roasted poultry.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Special occasions and lovers of classic California Chardonnay style</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Kumeu River Estate Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Auckland, New Zealand | ~$35</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Master of Wine Michael Brajkovich crafts this Burgundian-style Chardonnay using indigenous yeasts and minimal intervention techniques. The wine exhibits remarkable tension between ripe fruit and mineral precision, with subtle oak integration that allows the maritime terroir to shine through.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Wine enthusiasts seeking New World elegance and food-friendly sophistication</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Kongsgaard Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Napa Valley, California | ~$85</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">John Kongsgaard's minimalist approach yields one of California's most distinctive Chardonnays, fermented in neutral French oak with extended lees aging. This wine combines power with restraint, offering honeyed richness balanced by crisp minerality and remarkable aging potential.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Collectors and special celebrations requiring an iconic California producer</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Domaine Michel Bouzereau Meursault</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Meursault, Burgundy | ~$75</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">This village-level Meursault from a respected family domaine showcases the appellation's signature combination of power and finesse. Aged in 20% new French oak, it develops hazelnut and butter notes while maintaining the limestone-driven minerality that defines great white Burgundy.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Burgundy enthusiasts and elegant dinner parties with rich French cuisine</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Peay Vineyards Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Sonoma Coast, California | ~$48</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">From extreme coastal vineyards just four miles from the Pacific, this hidden gem expresses pure Sonoma Coast character with vibrant acidity and mineral complexity. The cool climate produces a wine with citrus precision and subtle oak, representing exceptional value from this cult producer.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Adventurous wine lovers seeking undiscovered coastal California excellence</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Felton Road Block 2 Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Central Otago, New Zealand | ~$55</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">This biodynamically farmed Chardonnay from Central Otago's unique schist soils offers an entirely different expression of the variety. Wild yeast fermentation and extended lees contact create a wine with remarkable textural complexity, combining stone fruit intensity with pristine mineral finish.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Wine geeks exploring unique terroir expressions and sustainable viticulture</p>
  </div>
</div>


<h2>More Excellent Options</h2>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Domaine William Fèvre Chablis</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Chablis, Burgundy | ~$25</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">This benchmark Chablis delivers the mineral-driven purity that made Chardonnay famous, with razor-sharp acidity and subtle notes of green apple and wet stone. Fèvre's sustainable viticulture and precise winemaking showcase the Kimmeridgian soil's influence, creating a wine that's both refreshing and complex.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Seafood dinners and those seeking classic Old World expression</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Bogle Vineyards Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">California Central Coast | ~$18</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Family-owned Bogle crafts this exceptional value Chardonnay using partial malolactic fermentation and light oak aging to create balance between fruit and structure. Expect ripe pear and apple flavors with vanilla undertones and crisp acidity that makes it incredibly food-friendly.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Everyday drinking and casual entertaining</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Cloudy Bay Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Marlborough, New Zealand | ~$45</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">From the pioneers of Marlborough winemaking, this Chardonnay combines fruit from various microclimates across the region, aged in French oak with regular lees stirring. The result is a wine with vibrant citrus and stone fruit flavors, balanced by creamy texture and a distinctive mineral finish that reflects the region's unique terroir.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Wine enthusiasts exploring international styles</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">Ramey Wine Cellars Russian River Valley Chardonnay</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Russian River Valley, California | ~$52</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">David Ramey's meticulous approach includes native yeast fermentation and 11 months aging in French oak, creating a wine that perfectly balances power and elegance. The cool Russian River Valley climate produces intense fruit concentration while maintaining bright acidity, resulting in layers of tropical fruit, citrus, and subtle spice.</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Special occasions and collectors seeking proven pedigree</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
