  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">Which Chardonnay regions offer the best value for money?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Washington State, particularly Columbia Valley, produces exceptional Chardonnays at $15-25 that rival $40+ Burgundies, offering bright acidity and mineral complexity. Chile's Casablanca Valley delivers outstanding cool-climate Chardonnays under $20, while Australia's Adelaide Hills provides elegant, food-friendly options. For premium value, look to Oregon's Willamette Valley where top producers offer Burgundian-style wines at half the price of their French counterparts.</p>
